<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62ae04ae-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s2906"><num value="2906">§ 2906.</num><heading> Use of English</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed as precluding the use of Federal funds to teach English to Native Americans.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62ae04af-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/477/tI/s107">Pub. L. 101–477, title I, § 107</ref>, <date date="1990-10-30">Oct. 30, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1156">104 Stat. 1156</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
